
1. Initialize the project:

```bash
npm install
```

1. Build all outputs:

```bash
npm run build:all
```

1. Test the bundles locally:

```bash
# Create a test HTML file to verify browser bundle
echo '<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <script src="https://unpkg.com/@solana/web3.js@latest/lib/index.iife.min.js"></script>
  <script src="./dist/browser/solana-kyc-compliance.min.js"></script>
</head>
<body>
  <script>
    console.log("SDK loaded:", window.SolanaKYC);
  </script>
</body>
</html>' > test-browser.html
```

ðŸ”§ Key Configuration Decisions

1. Dual Module Support: Both ESM (modern) and CJS (legacy) outputs
2. Tree-shaking Ready: Side-effect-free modules for optimal bundler optimization
3. Browser Compatibility: IIFE bundle for script tag usage
4. Type Safety: Complete TypeScript declarations with source maps
5. Performance: Terser minification and dead code elimination
6. Modular Imports: Subpath exports for partial SDK usage